data.enText: a solid figure that is completely round, with every point on its surface at an equal distance from the centre
any object that is completely round, for example a ball
an area of activity, influence or interest; a particular section of society

data.chText: 这一地区先前属于美国的势力范围。
data.enText: This area was formerly within the sphere of influence of the US.

data.chText: 我和他处在完全不同的社会圈子里。
data.enText: He and I moved in totally different social spheres.
a region that surrounds a planet, especially the earth

tr: a particular aspect of life or activity
example: he was helpless in an important sector of his life

tr: the apparent surface of the imaginary sphere on which celestial bodies appear to be projected
the geographical area in which one nation is very influential
a three-dimensional closed surface such that every point on the surface is equidistant from the center
a solid figure bounded by a spherical surface (including the space it encloses)
a particular environment or walk of life
example: it was a closed area of employment

value.def: A sphere is an object that is completely round in shape like a ball.
A sphere of activity or interest is a particular area of activity or interest.

example.ex: ...nurses, working in all spheres of the health service.
example.tran: 在公共医疗保健服务业的各领域工作的护士们

value.def: A sphere of people is a group of them who are similar in social status or who have the same interests.

example.ex: ...the realities of life outside the government and academic spheres of society.
example.tran: 政府和学术界以外社会阶层的生活现状

value.tran: (社会地位或兴趣等相同的)人群，阶层，圈子

value.def: A country's sphere of influence is an area of the world where it has a lot of influence.

example.ex: They see the region as their natural sphere of influence due to their historical links and a shared language.
example.tran: 基于历史上的联系和共同的语言，他们把该地区看成是自己天然的势力范围。

example.ex: ...countries traditionally within the British or American spheres of influence.
example.tran: 传统上处于英国或美国势力范围内的国家

value.tran: (国家的)势力范围，影响所及的范围

trans: (国家的)势力范围，影响所及的范围

partsOfSpeech.dec: atmo 空气 + sphere 球 → 围绕地球的空气 → 大气层
bio 生命 + spher 球 + e → 生物圈
chromo 颜色 + spher 球 + e → 色球
hemi 半 + spher 球 + e → 半球
spher 球 + ical …的 → 球形的
spher 球 + icity 具备某种性质，状况 → 球状
spher 球 + ics …学 → 球面几何学
spher 球 + oid …体 → 球（状）体
spher 球 + ule 小 → 小球（体）
